    <Folder>
      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The synthesized intelligence assessment reveals a U.S. military posture marked by sustained high operational tempo across multiple theaters, with particular emphasis on the Indo-Pacific and Middle East regions. Carrier strike groups and amphibious ready groups remain forward-deployed, with USS Carl Vinson operating in the South China Sea and USS America conducting amphibious readiness training with Philippine allies during Balikatan 2026 exercises. The MQ-25A Stingray&#39;s early operational testing represents a significant milestone in unmanned carrier aviation, enhancing long-range strike and refueling capabilities. Strategic airlift and ISR missions remain robust, with persistent surveillance flights over Europe and the Middle East indicating sustained monitoring requirements. The presence of multiple tanker aircraft (C130, K35R, A332) at high altitudes supports global power projection operations. Naval deployments show a balanced distribution between maintenance cycles and active operations, with 291 vessels underway representing approximately 75% of the total battle force. The Western Pacific remains a critical focus amid regional tensions, while the Arabian Sea continues to demand significant naval resources due to escalating Strait of Hormuz transit policy disputes. The data indicates a military preparing for prolonged high-intensity operations across multiple domains, with particular attention to unmanned systems integration and regional deterrence strategies. The integration of Marine Rotational Force-Darwin&#39;s certification as a Special Purpose Marine Air-Ground Task Force further enhances expeditionary capabilities in the Indo-Pacific theater.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
